**Tech stack**

This project follows a standardized and opinionated front-end stack to ensure consistency, maintainability, and modern best practices across the codebase.

- Yarn@v1.22 – Preferred package manager for dependency management and scripts.
- Vite – Fast and modern build tool for local development and bundling.
- TypeScript@5.5 – Statically typed JavaScript for improved code reliability and scalability.
- Prettier@^3 – Code formatter to enforce consistent styling.
- ESLint@^8 – Linter for identifying and fixing code quality issues.
- Tailwind CSS@3 – Utility-first CSS framework for rapid UI development.
- Daisy-UI@^4 – Tailwind CSS plugin for pre-styled UI components.
- React.js@^18 – Core UI library for building interactive UIs.
- React Router@^7 – Declarative routing solution used as the project’s navigation framework.
- Jotai@^2 – Primitive and flexible state management solution.
- Lodash – Utility library for common operations.
- react-icons – Collection of popular icon packs as React components.
- @hello-pangea/dnd – Drag-and-drop library based on react-beautiful-dnd, used for interactive reordering.
- react-hook-form@^7 – Lightweight and performant form state management library.
